txt.en:
[placeholder],

In the north, through the Ram Dúath, there is an encampment of Hillmen who have been free of Angmar's sway for years. My leader has trained some of these men, but we are in need of aid.

Seek me out at Aughaire, the encampment on the northern edge of the Ram Dúath. I am in a tent among a circle of stones.

Corunir

'I am glad to see you.\n\n'You should make your way among the people here. They will not shy from you. There is much that needs doing here and they will be grateful for any aid. This place is in dire need, friend.'
A letter from a Ranger hiding in the north among a band of Hillmen who have thrown free the yoke of Angmar tells that they are in need of help beyond the Ram Dúath.
Aughaire is an encampment of Hillmen, north through the Ram Dúath.\n\nCorunir's letter requests aid for the warriors standing against the oppressive Angmarim.
